@nobrowser
Feature: Managing Documents


Scenario Outline: Allocate A Document To An Item
    GIVEN a document exists
        AND an item exists
    WHEN <role> allocates this document to the item
    THEN the document is <state> to the item

    Examples:
        | role                               | state         |
        | Documentation, Engineering, public | allocated     |
        | public                             | not allocated |


Scenario Outline: Delete Item Allocation Of A Document
    GIVEN a document exists
        AND an item exists
        AND the document is allocated to the item
    WHEN <role> deletes the allocation of this document to the item
    THEN the allocation of the document to the item is <state>

    Examples:
        | role                               | state      |
        | Documentation, Engineering, public | deleted     |
        | public                             | not deleted |


Scenario Outline: Copy a Document allocated to an Item
    GIVEN a document exists
        AND an item exists
        AND the document is allocated to the item
    WHEN <role> copies this document
    THEN a new document is <action>
        AND no new item is generated
        AND the copy is <state> to the item

    Examples:
        | role                       | action        | state        |
        | Documentation, Engineering | generated     | allocated     |
        | public                     | not generated | not allocated |
